latestPosts.caption:
Today I did something I was truly scared of,
My first box jump. My mind was racing, my fears were screaming, and every part of me wanted to give up. But after countless tries and a lot of self-talk, I finally did it. A small win on the outside, but a massive victory inside.
It was my first attempt, and now that I’m a little more used to it, I’m hoping to do it cleaner and better in the coming days.
A big thanks to my trainer who made endless modifications to help me adapt, made it easier and more comfortable for me. Truly grateful for him 🙌 
Thank you so much, sir! @labib_malik_fitness 
Happy, proud, and a little stronger today! 💪
.
.
.
